  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3 re-evaluation)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This re-evaluation elevates the model risk level to 3 following expanded regulatory scrutiny of tolerance-sensitivity results. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are fully assessed and meet required levels. The 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor is recorded as not-assessed on the basis that direct parameter mapping between the CFD boundary conditions and the physical test rig is considered self-evident by the analysis team and therefore deemed outside the scope of formal assessment. No factorStatus of 'not-applicable' is applied because the team did not formally invoke the scoping-out procedure.",
